# Step 10: Create ClusterIssuer

Create:

```bash id="lab634"
vim clusterissuer.yaml
```

---

# clusterissuer.yaml

```yaml id="lab635"
apiVersion: cert-manager.io/v1
kind: ClusterIssuer

metadata:
  name: letsencrypt-prod

spec:
  acme:
    email: admin@rpn-labs.in

    server: https://acme-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory

    privateKeySecretRef:
      name: letsencrypt-prod

    solvers:
    - http01:
        gatewayHTTPRoute:
          parentRefs:
          - name: microk8s-gateway
            namespace: default
            kind: Gateway
```

Apply:

```bash id="lab636"
kubectl apply -f clusterissuer.yaml
```

---

# Step 11: Create Certificate

Create:

```bash id="lab637"
vim certificate.yaml
```

---

# certificate.yaml

```yaml id="lab638"
apiVersion: cert-manager.io/v1
kind: Certificate

metadata:
  name: rpn-labs-tls

spec:
  secretName: rpn-labs-tls

  issuerRef:
    name: letsencrypt-prod
    kind: ClusterIssuer

  dnsNames:
  - red.rpn-labs.in
  - blue.rpn-labs.in
  - green.rpn-labs.in
```

Apply:

```bash id="lab639"
kubectl apply -f certificate.yaml
```

